Veteran actor and producer Jide Kosoko has advised fans and followers on ways to feel privileged even feeling bad. In an Instagram message, Kosoko said many people feel bad when people remember them only when they need them. He said: “Don’t feel bad if people remember you only when they need you. Instead, feel privileged like a lamp that comes to their mind when they are in darkness.”   Fathia Balogun plans ‘birthday of the year’     Wizkid’s ‘Made In Lagos’ album gets Silver Brit…     Obi Cubana offers Lagos hawker university scholarship,…   On Wednesday, January 12, 2021, Kosoko turned 68 and he had his famous children, Sola and Bidemi, celebrating him alongside other film stars. - Advertisement - Kosoko, a good friend and colleague of Adebayo Salami aka Oga Bello, share the same birth day with Mrs Adebayo.